Good pho place in Silver Spring, easy to find - it's on Georgia avenue where metro tracks cross it over the bridge. If you're driving from DC you need right turn on Sligo. It's family own Vietnamese restaurant with about 12 types of pho plus some variations of Chinese dishes. Pho broth is pretty heavy so if you prefer lighter one look for Pho Than Binh on Collesvile road. Couple other notes - they do have full bar including bar stools and TV, small parking area and lunch specials. Be warn, if you ask for a shot it will be like double or triple one and usually no ice. Prices are pretty good if you stay with pho - large bowl plus a shot or beer will set you for about $15 or even less. Can't say that about Chinese dishes except for lunch specials. But seafood ones are good. Also the interior is pretty dated (think about pho place in Saigon). It's unusual experience if you're not accustomed to such places - worth to visit and enjoy good food. Final note - order pho and a shot of Stoli, add that to your bowl and enjoy.
